body:
Help wanted!
@jakubgs @jrainville @alexjba I've created a branch from this [PR](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/10210) to test x86_64 builds for Mac. And what i've discovered: this version runs fine locally, using `make package` with x86_64 Qt version 5.15.2. And it same time CI x86_64 [package]() for this PR hangs same way as described in ticket. Any ideas?

@anastasiyaig Can i kindly ask you to confirm that [this](https://ci.status.im/job/status-desktop/job/branches/job/macos/job/x86_64/job/package/view/change-requests/job/PR-10383/) package does not work, and locally built package for this [PR](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/10383) works fine

@MishkaRogachev Qt maintenance tool will install 5.15.2 and it can't be reproduced on that version. We've been using 5.15.2 for some time now without issues, but now the Qt was upgraded to 5.15.8 on CI machines to align the version with the arm version.

It looks like this is a known issue in Qt and the threaded renderer support was dropped since 5.12 for MacOs. Apparently it's unstable because MacOs will expect the app to render on the main thread and we're entering in a deadlock.

https://codereview.qt-project.org/c/qt/qtbase/+/245306

Since the threaded renderer is known to be unstable I'd say to disable it on MacOs even if it works fine on Intel Macs.

This code comment from Qt describes the issue quite well:
```
    case ThreadedOpenGL:
        // AppKit expects rendering to happen on the main thread, and we can
        // easily end up in situations where rendering on secondary threads
        // will result in visual artifacts, bugs, or even deadlocks, when
        // building with SDK 10.14 or higher which enbles view layer-backing.
        return QMacVersion::buildSDK() < QOperatingSystemVersion(QOperatingSystemVersion::MacOSMojave);
```
